column5: well folks i had two great lads fishing with me from Ohio and boy they fished hard,i was impressed that they never gave up .......even when i did  ,i think we caught 2 walleye and 2 pike for the whole week-end.  im sad to say we went out this morn and they bite ok we iced 1 10lb+ eye and 1 8-9lber and a 3lber plus missed 3 walleye at the top of the hole. never in my last 10 years have i had such a week end as that,these fellas not only smashed there car up in t.o during the storm that just past but fished there hearts out for what i call nothing  . ill post some pics later when i get back off the ice tonight taker easy Hawg Hunter
~~~Ya I remmber those guys, on Sat. morning, 2 real great guys, they were here to phish, and that's all that mattered, the car problem was secondaire.
Thanks for the update H.H.  Do you anticipate the ice remaining stable through this warm spell and safe for the weekend?
